President Obama has nominated Raymond T. Chen and Todd M. Hughes to serve on the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit. Raymond T. Chen is currently the Deputy General Counsel for Intellectual Property Law and Solicitor for the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO). He has extensive experience in intellectual property law and has represented the USPTO in numerous appeals before the Federal Circuit. Todd M. Hughes is the Deputy Director of the Commercial Litigation Branch of the Civil Division at the United States Department of Justice. He has experience in federal personnel law, veterans' benefits, international trade, and government contracts. Both nominees have demonstrated exceptional dedication to public service throughout their careers.